<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏘️ Builder Basics — Complete Your Village (Extension · Intermediate)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Bring It All Together · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate · <strong>Type:</strong> Extension Activity · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧩 This is a bonus challenge, not a weekly lesson. Try it after the Week 8 village project, once you can build with loops and move the agent between spots.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · The Challenge 🎯</h2>
<p>Finish your village so it feels like a place someone could live. There is no map — <strong>you</strong> choose the sizes and where things go. It must have <strong>all four</strong>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🏠 A <strong>house with a roof</strong>
🪣 A <strong>well</strong>
💧 A <strong>small pond</strong>
🌸 A <strong>small flower bed</strong></p>
<p>⚠️ One rule: <strong>everything is built with code.</strong> No placing blocks by hand.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Why does "build it with code" matter more than just how it looks?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Plan the Four Parts ✏️</h2>
<p>Fill in the table. For each structure, note the main block you will use and whether it needs a loop.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Structure</th>
<th>Main block(s)</th>
<th>Loop? (yes / no)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>🏠 House + roof</td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>🪣 Well</td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>💧 Small pond</td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>🌸 Small flower bed</td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pick the two hardest structures to build. What makes each one tricky?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Think in Loops 🔁</h2>
<p>A loop is for anything you repeat — a row of wall blocks, a row of flowers, the four sides of a well.</p>
<p><strong>Choose one structure. Describe the loop: what does it repeat, and how many times?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Between one structure and the next, what must the agent do so builds don't land on top of each other?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Go to your homework world and build. Run your code one structure at a time and move the agent between them. Keep going until the village has <strong>the house with a roof, the well, the small pond, and the small flower bed</strong> — all placed by code.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
